The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. A schema describing blood chemistry analysis of patients collected using a Piccolo Xpress analyzer in the Center for Viral Systems Biology.

Alanine Aminotransferase (ALT) measurement in U/L. Typical values are 10-47 U/L and dynamic range of the assay is 5-2000 U/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Albumin (ALB) measurement in g/L. Typical values are 33-55 g/L and dynamic range of the assay is 10-65 g/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Alkaline Phosphatase (ALP) measurement in U/L. Typical values are 53-128 U/L (male) or 42-141 U/L (female) and dynamic range of the assay is 5-2400 U/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Aspartate Aminotransferase (AST) measurement in U/L. Typical values are 11-38 U/L and dynamic range of the assay is 5-2000 U/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Blood Urea Nitrogen (BUN) measurement in mmol urea/L. Typical values are 2.5-7.9 mmol urea/L and dynamic range of the assay is 0.7-64.3 mmol urea/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Calcium (CA) measurement in mmol/L. Typical values are 2.0-2.58 mmol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 1.0-4.0 mmol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Chloride (CL-) measurement in mmol/L. Typical values are 98-108 mmol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 80-135 mmol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Creatinine (CRE) measurement in umol/L. Typical values are and 53-106 umol/L dynamic range of the assay is 18-1768 umol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Glucose (GLU) measurement in mmol/L. Typical values are 4.05-6.55 mmol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 0.56-38.9 mmol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Potassium (K+) measurement in mmol/L. Typical values are 3.6-5.1 mmol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 1.5-8.5 mmol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Sodium (NA+) measurement in mmol/L. Typical values are 128-145 mmol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 110-170 mmol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Total Bilirubin (TBIL) measurement in umol/L. Typical values are 3.4-27.4 umol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 1.7-513 umol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Total Carbon Dioxide (tCO2) measurement in mmol/L. Typical values are 18-33 mmol/L and dynamic range of the assay is 5-40 mmol/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.

Total Protein (TP) measurement in g/L. Typical values are 64-81 g/L and dynamic range of the assay is 20-140 g/L (https://www.abaxis.com/sites/default/files/resource-packages/Comprehensive%20Metabolic%20Panel%20Package%20Insert-EN_0.pdf). If values are outside the dynamic range, they should be reported as missing.
